My trip to #MountVernon yesterday to pay my respects to those that lived there and those that were enslaved was a day I'll never forget. I'm grateful for another opportunity to learn about our history as a country. Everything I learned, good or evil, gives me knowledge on how to better myself as a human being and an ally. Thank you to the Mount Vernon Ladies' Association of the Union for all you do to help preserve George Washington's home, his legacy, and the legacy of the enslaved people of Mount Vernon. We will always remember all who were a part of it thanks to you. 

If you haven't been to Mount Vernon before I highly recommend a visit. Give yourself at least half a day to walk the entire grounds and learn all you can about its legacy. @mount_vernon #MountVernon

I'll be back soon for some more exploration on this beautiful island. Mahalo to everyone that welcomed us and guided us around Hawaii'i.
